byline.contributor: Majd Al Waheidi contributed reporting from the Gaza Strip.

abstract: Palestinian youths and Israeli police clash inside Jerusalem's Al Aqsa Mosque, contested holy site revered by Muslims as Noble Sanctuary and by Jews as Temple Mount; police say Palestinians were trying to prevent Israelis from visiting site on eve of Rosh Hashana, Jewish New Year.
lead_paragraph: Young Palestinians clashed with Israeli police officers who entered the compound in what appears to have become an increasingly familiar occurrence on the eve of Jewish holidays.

headline.main: On Eve of Holiday, Israeli Police and Palestinians Clash at Al Aqsa Mosque
headline.print_headline: On Eve of Holiday, Israeli Police and Palestinians Clash at Holy Site
